The Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN) has commended President Muhammadu Buhari’s approach to the current coronavirus situation in Nigeria, praying for the speedy recovery of infected persons in the country. In a statement signed by IPMAN’s national president, Alhaji Sanusi Fari, the group said the measures rolled out by the federal government are enough to break the circle of spread of the pandemic that recently took the life of one of their former colleagues, an ex-MD of PPMC. According to Alhaji Sanusi, ‘‘The measures he (Buhari) rolled out are capable and can stop the spread of this pandemic, COVID-19’’. ‘‘We, like every other Nigerian are calling on our members to sacrifice by obeying the directives of Mr. President. ‘‘We have directed our members to continue operation in line with the directives of Mr. President by ensuring that our petrol stations remain open while observing the strict guidelines from our health authorities.” Alhaji Sanusi added that while the group remains grateful to NUPENG’s President, Comrade Williams Akporeha and his executives, NARTO President, Alhaji Yusuf Othman and his executive and National Chairman, PTD of NUPENG, Comrade Salimon Oladiti for their cooperation so far, he called on PEF Board to continue payment of marketers’ bridging claims as promised to lessen their burden especially at this time to enable them to continue to provide service to the public in the interest of the country.